               <p>751. <persName id="def1-751-18771022" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-751-18771022" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-751-18771022" type="age" value="26"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-751-18771022" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-751-18771022" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ROBERT JONES</hi> (26)</persName>, was indicted<rs id="t18771022-751-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18771022-751-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18771022-751-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for unlawfully uttering counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. LLOYD</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. AUSTIN METCALFE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-27" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-27" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-27" type="surname" value="SANSAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-27" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY SANSAM</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman S</hi> 289). On the afternoon of 7th September I was at the Bull and Butcher public-house, Whetstone, in plain clothes, except a pair of blue trousers—Jones came in, and called for a glass of ale, and tendered a florin—the barmaid brought it back bent—and I went after the prisoner, and saw him one hundred yards from the house talking to the prisoner Beattie—(<hi rend="italic">see next case</hi>)—on seeing me he went off; I followed, and said "Have you had a glass of ale?"—he said that he went in—I said "The florin is bad; you had better come back and see about it"—Beattie then stopped—I said "You had better come back as well"—he said "Me"—I said "Yes, you"—going the police-station Jones said "Lot my mate go, he has nothing to do with it"—the prisoner was taken to the station and charged—Mr. Goodwin, the landlord of the public-house, gave me a bag containing eight counterfeit florins besides the one that was passed—I searched Jones, and found on him two good half-crowns, an albert, a locket, 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and three pawn tickets—I found a half-sovereign on Beattie.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by the Prisoner.</hi> The coin was put into the till in my presence—I waited to see the coin tried, and then followed you.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-28" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-28" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-28" type="surname" value="OLMIT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-28" type="given" value="EMILY"></interp>EMILY OLMIT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am barmaid at the Bull and Butcher—the prisoner tailed for a glass of ale, and tendered a florin—I put it in a corner of the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187710220004"></xptr>
               <p>drawer, and when he went out I tried it, and bent it, and gave it to the constable—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> The other money in the till was in a bowl—there was no other large money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-29" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-29" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-29" type="surname" value="GOODWIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-29" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE GOODWIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Bull and Butcher—in consequence of what was said to me I went to Whetstone police-station—the policeman brought Jones and Beattie along—on going in I saw a little black bag in Beattie's left hand, which he dropped in a back garden—I picked it up, and gave it to the constable—I was only five yards away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-30" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-30" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-30" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-30" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. This is a bad florin—the others are bad, five of them being of the same mould.</p>
               <p>[<hi rend="italic">The prisoner's statement before the Magistrate was that he met</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">BEATTIE</hi>, <hi rend="italic">who was a stranger, and asked him the way to the station, when the constable came—he made a similar statement in his defence.</hi>]</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18771022-751-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
